# Git — Push After Every Commit

When you create a git commit in this repository, **push it to the remote** in the same workflow. Do not leave commits only on the local machine unless the user explicitly asks not to push.

## Agent workflow

1. Create the commit (only when the user asked for a commit).
2. Push to the tracked upstream branch: `git push` (use `-u origin <branch>` if no upstream is set).
3. Confirm push succeeded (`git status` should not show "ahead of origin").

## Safety

- Never `git push --force` to `main` or `master` unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Never update git config.
- If push is rejected (non-fast-forward, auth, hooks), report the error and stop; do not force-push unless explicitly asked.

## Exceptions

Skip push only when the user clearly says not to push (e.g. "commit but don't push yet").
